?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxUdWx1bSUyMHJ1aW5zJTIwQ2FyaWJiZWFuJTIwY2xpZmZ8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4Mzc4NzUzOHww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080"}],"top10":[{"rank":1,"name":"Cancún","placeId":"cancun","regionId":"yucatan_peninsula","regionName":"Yucatan Peninsula (Quintana Roo, Yucatán & Campeche)","image":null,"description":"Mexico's premier Caribbean resort destination with pristine beaches, turquoise waters, and world-class hotels. The main hub for accessing the Riviera Maya and a gateway to Mayan ruins, cenotes, and natural wonders."},{"rank":2,"name":"Mexico City","placeId":"mexico_city","regionId":"central_mexico","regionName":"Central Mexico (Mexico State, Puebla & Tlaxcala)","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1627417573707-f23a941968d1?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxNZXhpY28lMjBDaXR5JTIwWiVDMyVCM2NhbG98ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4Mzc4MzQ5Nnww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Kathy Lara"},"description":"The capital and largest city of Mexico, built on the ruins of the Aztec capital Tenochtitlan, featuring world-class museums, historic plazas, and vibrant neighborhoods. A must-visit for its Templo Mayor, Museo Frida Kahlo, Palacio Nacional murals, and bustling cultural scene."},{"rank":3,"name":"Playa del Carmen","placeId":"playa_del_carmen","regionId":"yucatan_peninsula","regionName":"Yucatan Peninsula (Quintana Roo, Yucatán & Campeche)","image":null,"description":"A vibrant beach town with a famous pedestrian promenade (Quinta Avenida), excellent dining, shopping, and nightlife on pristine Caribbean shores. The ideal base for exploring the Riviera Maya with easy access to cenotes, ruins, and island excursions."},{"rank":4,"name":"Puerto Vallarta","placeId":"puerto_vallarta","regionId":"west_coast","regionName":"West Coast (Jalisco, Nayarit & Colima)","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1736888982439-837c1aeae4fe?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxQdWVydG8lMjBWYWxsYXJ0YSUyME1hbGVjJUMzJUIzbiUyMHN1bnNldHxlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzgzNzgzNTM2fDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Ondrej Bocek"},"description":"Mexico's most famous Pacific resort town, Puerto Vallarta combines colonial charm with modern amenities, set against dramatic jungle-clad mountains and a beautiful bay. The cobblestone Malecón waterfront, galleries, restaurants, and beaches make it the cultural and gastronomic heart of the west coast."},{"rank":5,"name":"Chichén Itzá","placeId":"chichen_itza","regionId":"yucatan_peninsula","regionName":"Yucatan Peninsula (Quintana Roo, Yucatán & Campeche)","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1561577101-aa749bffbb70?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxDaGljaCVDMyVBOW4lMjBJdHolQzMlQTElMjBFbCUyMENhc3RpbGxvJTIwcHlyYW1pZHxlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzgzNzg3NTQwfDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Christina Abken"},"description":"One of the New Seven Wonders of the World and the most visited archaeological site in Mexico, featuring the iconic stepped pyramid El Castillo. This UNESCO World Heritage Site represents the pinnacle of Mayan architectural and astronomical achievement."},{"rank":6,"name":"Cozumel","placeId":"cozumel","regionId":"yucatan_peninsula","regionName":"Yucatan Peninsula (Quintana Roo, Yucatán & Campeche)","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1603550255182-866239fb37e7?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxDb3p1bWVsJTIwY29yYWwlMjByZWVmJTIwZGl2aW5nfGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODM3ODc1NDR8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Tam Minton"},"description":"Mexico's premier dive destination with world-renowned coral reefs, colorful fish, and excellent visibility for snorkeling and scuba diving. This island offers a more relaxed alternative to mainland resorts with pristine beaches and rich marine biodiversity."},{"rank":7,"name":"Guadalajara","placeId":"guadalajara","regionId":"west_coast","regionName":"West Coast (Jalisco, Nayarit & Colima)","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1563657296501-c3770ae0057b?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxHdWFkYWxhamFyYSUyMENhdGhlZHJhbCUyMFBsYXphJTIwZGUlMjBBcm1hc3xlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzgzNzgzNTQyfDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Roman Lopez"},"description":"Mexico's second-largest city and the birthplace of mariachi music and tequila culture, Guadalajara offers world-class museums, colonial plazas, and authentic Mexican cuisine. Though inland, it's the cultural epicenter of Jalisco and an essential counterpoint to coastal tourism."},{"rank":8,"name":"Acapulco","placeId":"acapulco","regionId":"pacific_coast","regionName":"Pacific Coast (Michoacán, Guerrero & Oaxaca Coast)","image":null,"description":"Mexico's most famous beach resort set in a dramatic crescent bay surrounded by mountains and jungle. Known for its iconic cliff divers, nightlife, luxury resorts, and as a historic glamorous destination that shaped Mexican beach culture."},{"rank":9,"name":"Teotihuacán","placeId":"teotihuacan","regionId":"central_mexico","regionName":"Central Mexico (Mexico State, Puebla & Tlaxcala)","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1733160791918-aca600db0f75?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxQeXJhbWlkJTIwb2YlMjB0aGUlMjBTdW4lMjBUZW90aWh1YWMlQzMlQTFufGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODM3ODM1MjJ8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Thomas Gabernig"},"description":"One of the world's largest pre-Hispanic city ruins featuring the iconic Pyramids of the Sun and Moon and the Avenue of the Dead, offering insights into an advanced pre-Aztec civilization. Its monumental scale and mysterious history make it one of Mexico's most visited archaeological sites."},{"rank":10,"name":"Xcaret","placeId":"xcaret","regionId":"yucatan_peninsula","regionName":"Yucatan Peninsula (Quintana Roo, Yucatán & Campeche)","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1558445339-7f1ebdc38ccf?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxYY2FyZXQlMjBlY28lMjBwYXJrJTIwTWV4aWNvfGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODM3ODc1NDh8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Alex Braga"},"description":"An extensive eco-archaeological park combining natural attractions like cenotes, underground rivers, and beaches with cultural shows and Mayan heritage experiences. A major tourist destination offering family-friendly activities across beautiful jungle and coastal terrain."}]}